  <dcvalue element="description" qualifier="learningOutcome" language="en_US">This activity is designed to give students practice in developing a hypothesis, visualization and statistical analysis of large datasets, and interpretation of the results.  Students will apply their understanding of concepts in evolutionary biology, such as adaptive radiation and character displacement.  In addition, this activity is designed to give students experience in group work and presentation of their work.</dcvalue>
